<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">&gt;
<step><![CDATA[Bring to boil carrots in water, then reduce and cook uncovered 35 m, until mixture is almost completely dry and sticky.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Bring to boil sugar in water, whisking a few times to encourage the sugar to dissolve then crumble saffron in, and pour the mixture over the carrots.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Simmer on low hear for further 40 minutes until fat bubbles of air form on the surface as it cooks. Add rosewater for last 10 minutes. Remove the carrots from the heat and allow to cool]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Dry roast cardamom pods 3-4 minutes, crack them open and crush the black seeds to a fine powder, discarding the green husks. Stir into the jam to cool completely.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[When cool, place the jam in sterilised jars or store in bowls tightly covered in cling film in the fridge.]]></step>
&gt;</directions>
